{"title":"Combined feed","url":"https://Vinnl.github.io/feeds/all.xml","elements":[{"title":"speckled spiny tree-rat (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that of the three specimens used to <a href=\"/wiki/Species_description\" title=\"Species description\">describe</a> the <b><a href=\"/wiki/Speckled_spiny_tree-rat\" title=\"Speckled spiny tree-rat\">speckled spiny tree-rat</a></b> <i>(pictured)</i>, only part of a skull remains?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Speckled_spiny_tree-rat","retrieved":1781555831331},{"title":"Thomas Harvey (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that Leeds Quaker and chemist <b><a href=\"/wiki/Thomas_Harvey_(Quaker)\" title=\"Thomas Harvey (Quaker)\">Thomas Harvey</a></b> manufactured the first commercially available small clinical thermometer?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_Harvey_(Quaker)","retrieved":1781555831332},{"title":"a Mexico City metro station (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that in <b><a href=\"/wiki/Divisi%C3%B3n_del_Norte_metro_station\" title=\"División del Norte metro station\">a Mexico City metro station</a></b>, commuters can sing karaoke  or play the piano?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Divisi%C3%B3n_del_Norte_metro_station","retrieved":1781555831332},{"title":"The Dark Pictures Anthology: Man of Medan (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the developers of <i><b><a href=\"/wiki/The_Dark_Pictures_Anthology:_Man_of_Medan\" title=\"The Dark Pictures Anthology: Man of Medan\">The Dark Pictures Anthology: Man of Medan</a></b></i> held judgment-free \"death meetings\" to brainstorm unique death scenes for the characters?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Dark_Pictures_Anthology:_Man_of_Medan","retrieved":1781555831333},{"title":"a successful coup in New Caledonia (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that an Australian warship backed <b><a href=\"/wiki/Rallying_of_New_Caledonia_to_Free_France\" title=\"Rallying of New Caledonia to Free France\">a successful coup in New Caledonia</a></b> in 1940?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rallying_of_New_Caledonia_to_Free_France","retrieved":1781555831348},{"title":"Jaime Felipa (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Jaime_Felipa\" title=\"Jaime Felipa\">Jaime Felipa</a></b> worked as an airport security guard at Curaçao International Airport during his judo career?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jaime_Felipa","retrieved":1781555831349},{"title":"a Manhattan townhouse (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the designer of <b><a href=\"/wiki/Barbara_Rutherford_Hatch_House\" title=\"Barbara Rutherford Hatch House\">a Manhattan townhouse</a></b> \"succeeded in almost completely Mediterraneanizing\" the city block?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barbara_Rutherford_Hatch_House","retrieved":1781555831350},{"title":"one of the best goals (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <a href=\"/wiki/Toluca_FC\" title=\"Toluca FC\">Toluca FC</a> scored what is widely regarded to be <b><a href=\"/wiki/Toluca_FC_6%E2%80%930_Club_Am%C3%A9rica_(2003)\" title=\"Toluca FC 6–0 Club América (2003)\">one of the best goals</a></b> in <a href=\"/wiki/Liga_MX\" title=\"Liga MX\">Liga MX</a> history?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toluca_FC_6%E2%80%930_Club_Am%C3%A9rica_(2003)","retrieved":1781555831352},{"title":"Laughing Jacobs Creek (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Laughing_Jacobs_Creek\" title=\"Laughing Jacobs Creek\">Laughing Jacobs Creek</a></b> was reportedly named after an early settler's attempt to make a <a href=\"/wiki/Loon\" title=\"Loon\">loon</a> call?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laughing_Jacobs_Creek","retrieved":1781555831353},{"title":"Destination of the Month (Wikivoyage recommendations)","contents":"<span class=\"mw-empty-elt\" about=\"#mwt8\" typeof=\"mw:Transclusion\" id=\"mwIg\" data-mw=\"{&quot;parts&quot;:[{&quot;template&quot;:{&quot;t